blank\"><img \nsrc=\"http://f.e.newyorktimesinfo.com/i/18/2094298569/20141120_CRS_3895_cooking_thanksgiving_email_hero_567x678.jpg\" \nwidth=\"567\" height=\"678\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Let the preparations begin.\" \nstyle=\"display:block\"></a></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"567\" align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" style=\"padding:5px 5px 20px \n5px;font-family:Georgia, Times, \nserif;color:#363636;font-size:16px;font-weight:bold;font-style:italic;line-height:155%;\">Visit \n<a href=\"http://e.newyorktimesinfo.com/a/hBUbiMIB81HXJB89ub2AAwENcV6/nytcklink\" target=\"_blank\" \nstyle=\"text-decoration:none;color:#363636;\">nytcooking.com</a> and set \nthe stage for an<br>extraordinary Thanksgiving feast.</td>\n</tr>\n</table><!-- END MAIN IMAGE/SUBHEADER TABLE -->\n\n<!-- BEGIN ENTER THE KITCHEN TABLE -->\n<table width=\"567\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"0\" \nstyle=\"border-bottom: #000000 1px solid;\">\n<tr>\n<td width=\"300\" align=\"left\" valign=\"top\" style=\"font-family:Georgia, \nTimes, \nserif;color:#363636;font-size:13px;font-weight:normal;line-height:225%;padding-bottom:35px;\"><span \nstyle=\"font-style:italic;\">Shake up your side dishes. Consider a \ndifferent method of cooking the bird. Or embrace the traditional menu, \nwith a burnished turkey, pan gravy, stuffing and pie. No matter how \nyou&rsquo;re approaching the year&rsquo;s biggest meal, we have the \nrecipes, advice and instructions to guide you from appetizer to dessert \n&mdash; in one convenient location.</span>\n<br><br>\n<a \nhref=\"http://e.newyorktimesinfo.com/a/hBUbiMIB81HXJB89ub2AAwENcV6/kitchen02\" \ntarget=\"_blank\"><img \nsrc=\"http://f.e.newyorktimesinfo.com/i/18/2094298569/20141120_CRS_3895_cooking_thanksgiving_email_ENTERkitchen_290x36.jpg\" \nwidth=\"290\" height=\"36\" border=\"0\" alt=\"ENTER THE KITCHEN\" \nstyle=\"display:inline-block;background-color:#ff6d00;font-family:Arial, \nHelvetica, \nsans-serif;color:#FFFFFF;text-decoration:none;font-weight:bold;\"></a>\n</td>\n<td width=\"267\" align=\"left\" valign=\"top\">\n<!-- BEGIN BULLET TABLE -->\n<table width=\"267\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"0\">\n<tr>\n<td width=\"15\" align=\"left\" valign=\"top\" style=\"font-family:Georgia, \nTimes, \nserif;color:#ff6d00;font-size:13px;font-weight:normal;line-height:165%;\">&#9679;&nbsp;</td>\n<td width=\"252\" align=\"left\" valign=\"top\" style=\"font-family:Georgia, \nTimes, \nserif;color:#363636;font-size:13px;font-weight:normal;font-style:italic;line-height:165%;padding-bottom:25px;\"><span \nstyle=\"font-weight:bold;\">Your best turkey.</span> We give you our \ncooks&rsquo; time-tested formulas for success.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"15\" align=\"left\" valign=\"top\" style=\"font-family:Georgia, \nTimes, \nserif;color:#ff6d00;font-size:13px;font-weight:normal;line-height:165%;\">&#9679;&nbsp;</td>\n<td width=\"252\" align=\"left\" valign=\"top\" style=\"font-family:Georgia, \nTimes, \nserif;color:#363636;font-size:13px;font-weight:normal;font-style:italic;line-height:165%;padding-bottom:25px;\"><span \nstyle=\"font-weight:bold;\">Side dishes.</span> These recipes are a \nperfect complement to the main attraction.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"15\" align=\"left\" valign=\"top\" style=\"font-family:Georgia, \nTimes, \nserif;color:#ff6d00;font-size:13px;font-weight:normal;line-height:165%;\">&#9679;&nbsp;</td>\n<td width=\"252\" align=\"left\" valign=\"top\" style=\"font-family:Georgia, \nTimes, \nserif;color:#363636;font-size:13px;font-weight:normal;font-style:italic;line-height:165%;\"><span \nstyle=\"font-weight:bold;\">Thanksgiving pies.</span> Brandied pumpkin. \nPear pomegranate. Chocolate pecan. You&rsquo;ll find them all here.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"267\" colspan=\"2\" align=\"left\" valign=\"top\" \nstyle=\"padding-top:14px;\">\n<a \nhref=\"http://e.newyorktimesinfo.com/a/hBUbiMIB81HXJB89ub2AAwENcV6/app\" \ntarget=\"_blank\"><img \nsrc=\"http://f.e.newyorktimesinfo.com/i/18/2094298569/20141120_CRS_3895_cooking_thanksgiving_email_Apple_267x53.jpg\" \nwidth=\"267\" height=\"53\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Download on the App Store\" \nstyle=\"display:inline-block;\"></a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<!-- END BULLET TABLE -->\n</td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<!-- END ENTER THE KITCHEN TABLE -->\n\n<!-- BEGIN FIND YOUR STATE TABLE -->\n<table width=\"567\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"0\" \nstyle=\"border-bottom: #000000 1px solid;\">\n<tr>\n<td width=\"300\" align=\"left\" valign=\"top\" style=\"font-family:Georgia, \nTimes, \nserif;color:#363636;font-size:13px;font-weight:bold;line-height:175%;padding-bottom:35px;\"><img \nsrc=\"http://f.e.newyorktimesinfo.com/i/18/2094298569/20141120_CRS_3895_cooking_thanksgiving_email_introUS_300x110.jpg\" \nwidth=\"300\" height=\"110\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Introducing the United States \nod Thanksgiving...\" style=\"display:inline-block\"><br><span \nstyle=\"font-style:italic;\">Our cooks and reporters have spent months \nscouring the nation for Thanksgiving recipes that evoke each of the 50 \nstates, selecting one dish for each state. Dig into our picks, then tell \nus yours.</span>\n<br><br>\n<a \nhref=\"http://e.newyorktimesinfo.com/a/hBUbiMIB81HXJB89ub2AAwENcV6/state01\" \ntarget=\"_blank\"><img \nsrc=\"http://f.e.newyorktimesinfo.com/i/18/2094298569/20141120_CRS_3895_cooking_thanksgiving_email_FINDstate_290x49.jpg\" \nwidth=\"290\" height=\"49\" border=\"0\" alt=\"FIND YOUR STATE\" \nstyle=\"display:inline-block;background-color:#ff6d00;font-family:Arial, \nHelvetica, \nsans-serif;color:#FFFFFF;text-decoration:none;font-weight:bold;\"></a>\n</td>\n<td width=\"267\" align=\"left\" valign=\"top\">\n<a \nhref=\"http://e.newyorktimesinfo.com/a/hBUbiMIB81HXJB89ub2AAwENcV6/state02\" \ntarget=\"_blank\"><img \nsrc=\"http://f.e.newyorktimesinfo.com/i/18/2094298569/20141120_CRS_3895_cooking_thanksgiving_email_recipes_267x293.jpg\" \nwidth=\"267\" height=\"293\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Recipes\" \nstyle=\"display:block;\"></a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<!-- END FIND YOUR STATE TABLE -->\n\n<!-- BEGIN PINTEREST TABLE -->\n<table width=\"567\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"0\" \nstyle=\"padding-top:25px;padding-bottom:25px;\">\n<tr>\n<td width=\"48\" align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"><a \nhref=\"http://e.newyorktimesinfo.com/a/hBUbiMIB81HXJB89ub2AAwENcV6/pintrest01\" target=\"_blank\"><img \nsrc=\"http://f.e.newyorktimesinfo.com/i/18/2094298569/20141120_CRS_3895_cooking_thanksgiving_email_pinterest_48x39.jpg\" \nwidth=\"48\" height=\"39\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Pinterest\" \nstyle=\"display:block;\"></a></td>\n<td width=\"519\" align=\"left\" valign=\"top\" style=\"font-family:Georgia, \nTimes, \nserif;color:#363636;font-size:13px;font-weight:bold;line-height:165%;\"><span \nstyle=\"font-style:italic;\">We invite you to follow us on Pinterest where \nyou&rsquo;ll find our board filled with great recipes, and photos to \nmatch.</span>\n<br><br>\n<a href=\"http://e.newyorktimesinfo.com/a/hBUbiMIB81HXJB89ub2AAwENcV6/pintrest02\" target=\"_blank\"><img \nsrc=\"http://f.e.newyorktimesinfo.com/i/18/2094298569/20141120_CRS_3895_cooking_thanksgiving_email_pinTEREST_377x36.jpg\" \nwidth=\"377\" height=\"36\" border=\"0\" alt=\"WE INVITE YOU TO FOLLOW US ON \nPINTEREST\" style=\"display:inline-block;\"></a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n<!-- END PINTEREST TABLE -->\n<!-- END MAIN CONTENT TABLE -->\n\n<!-- BEGIN DISCLAIMER TABLE -->\n<table width=\"567\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"0\" \nstyle=\"border-top:#000000 1px solid;\">\n<tr>\n<td width=\"567\" align=\"left\" valign=\"top\" style=\"font-family:Helvetica, \nArial, Sans \nSerif;color:#666666;font-size:11px;font-weight:normal;line-height:125%;padding-top:25px;\">This \nemail was sent to you as a registered user on NYTimes.com.<br><br>App is \navailable on iPad only. Apple and the Apple logo are trademarks of Apple \nInc., registered in the U.S. and other countries. \u0003iPad is a trademark of \nApple Inc.\n<br><br>\nTo ensure delivery of